                  {
                    "value": "Consider where you place objects on the canvas. Using the Z-pattern is a good starting point. Users first look at the top left of the page, then to the top right, then down to the bottom left then across to the bottom right. ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "color": "#767676"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "By placing the most important or first needed (such as headings and filters), in the top left, users will look there first, then make their way down the report.",
